Anticipated Personal Care Assistants (PCA) needed at Keystone Central School District. High school diploma/GED required; must obtain "highly qualified" status within one (1) year from date of hire. "Highly Qualified" means having an associate's degree or higher; or having completed 2 years of post-secondary study; or meeting a rigorous standard of quality as demonstrated through a state or local assessment. All Personal Care Assistants must hold or obtain First Aid/CPR and JKM passive restraint certification (District will train) and keep same current. Contact the Human Resources office at 570-893-4900 ext. 2320 for more information.

Starting rate for Personal Care Assistants (PCAs) is $15.93/hr.

Apply online at https://www.applitrack.com/kcsd/onlineapp/

post_text:
Keystone Central School District is accepting applications for an anticipated Crisis Counselor.
Qualifications include a minimum master’s degree and appropriate Pennsylvania certification for Elementary/Secondary Guidance Counseling required; background in working with both elementary and secondary children; or a master’s degree is social work; must be an effective communicator, compassionate person with strong organizational and leadership skills.

The crisis counselor’s function is to support those students who are in a state of acute mental health crisis often brought on by a recent trauma or a long term case of Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (including but not limited to a pandemic, natural disaster, domestic violence, loss or abuse). The counselor will provide the student with support for a brief period of time, where they will provide emotional support and will teach the student coping strategies while emphasizing techniques that minimize constant stress. Position reports to the Director of Pupil Services.

post_text:
Hello All!

As the school year comes to a close, we are taking a long and in-depth look at what next year may hold. To help us to prepare for this, we have come up with a few tools!

For parents/guardians:
Please take a moment to fill out this "Reopening of Schools" survey that will provide us some insight into the 20-21 school year.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScII-iOcLxSBgoRfiDHkp55H0bj-TvqGsUg3vhpq2ZYsX1npQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

For Students grades 6-12:
Please take a moment to complete this feedback form so that we can gain a more in-depth understanding of our successes and our growing opportunities.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSezJDBLlBCl0J1Ao6tV8w0S7Osy-Pd6-DHu31hMOOaN-bfMLQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

We are asking that you please complete these forms by Friday, June 19, 2020 so that we can review the data to help us plan for next year.

post_text: Today, May 15, would have marked the 5th annual Mini-Thon held by Central Mountain Middle School. Due to COVID-19, this was just another event cancelled! Throughout the school year, the MT committee worked hard to raise funds that would be donated to the Four Diamonds Foundation. We will still be able to donate the money that was raised on donor drive and also thanks to the many business donations. The businesses listed below, made donations of over $200.00 this year. We can’t thank you enough for all your support throughout the years! Faculty, staff and students have always done an outstanding job at this event and we all miss it for sure, but we know Mini-Thon 2021 will be the best one yet! Thank everyone again! A total will be revealed at a later date!- Jaime Kessinger (CMMS) #FTK #fourdiamonds

post_text: After losing her grandmother last fall, Hannah Bradley, junior at Bucktail, began honoring her Nana's memory through original and meaningful artworks. Prior to the school closure, Hannah began composing her idea of releasing a symbolic butterfly into a vast landscape from her hands. Combining her photographs, Hannah sketched and added some color to the background. After weeks of hiatus from the painting, she was able to retrieve her unfinished artwork from school. Hannah was able to complete the painting this week just in time to meet her deadline of her grandmother's birthday, as a birthday present to her own mother. This is beautiful, Hannah! #kcsdproud
